headline: FOXA Q1 Earnings Call: Digital Investments, Super Bowl, and Direct-to-Consumer Strategy Highlight Quarter
summary: Cable news and media network Fox (NASDAQ:FOXA) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, but sales rose 26.8% year on year to $4.37 billion. Its non-GAAP EPS of $1.10 per share was 22.6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
